const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/maytag-washer-repair/";

const title = "Maytag Washer Repair, Same-Day Service Across Southern California";
const description = "Maytag washer repair across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino & Riverside counties. $89 dx. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 (#1346255700410).";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What's the difference between Maytag Bravos, Maxima, and Centennial washers?",
    a: "Three Maytag washer families on the shared Whirlpool platform. Bravos is the top-load HE family, most are impeller-driven (no agitator), with electronic controls. MVWB-series model numbers. Service tree mirrors Whirlpool Cabrio: lid lock (year 3-6), drain pump (year 6-9), drive belt + shift actuator (year 5-8), suspension rod kit (year 9+ for unbalanced loads), main control board (year 8-12). Maxima is the front-load family, MHW-series. Service tree mirrors Whirlpool Duet: drain pump (year 5-8), door boot (year 8-10), bearing + drum seal (year 8-12, $585-$880 with seal), main control board (CCU). Centennial is the entry-tier top-load, simpler architecture, drive-belt transmission, more mechanical-feeling. Centennial is actually the most reliable Maytag washer through year 10+ because it has fewer electronic components to fail. Commercial-Technology models (MVWP) sit at the top of the line with heavier-duty components."
  },
  {
    q: "What does an F01 / F02 / F11 / F26 error code mean on my Maytag washer?",
    a: "Same codes as Whirlpool washers because Maytag and Whirlpool share the platform. F01, main control board (CCU) communication or internal fault. Reset by unplugging for 10 minutes; if F01 returns, CCU replacement ($345-$525). F02, long drain error; the control didn't detect drain completion within 8 minutes. Drain pump, drain hose, or drain filter clog ($145-$385). F11, serial communication error between CCU and MCU; one of the boards or the harness between them ($345-$680). F26, door / lid switch error; lid lock on Bravos or door lock on Maxima ($145-$215 typical). About 70% of F26 codes resolve at lid/door lock replacement."
  },
  {
    q: "Are Maytag washers really \"built to last\"?",
    a: "Honest answer. Maytag's marketing positioning around durability is partially true, the heavier-duty Commercial-Technology models (MVWP) actually do use commercial-grade components and run longer than equivalent Whirlpool-branded entry-tier units. The Bravos top-load and Maxima front-load consumer lines are more typical mid-tier appliances, reliable, but not standout, and very similar to Whirlpool Cabrio and Duet equivalents because they share the same platform. Across all Maytag washers, the \"built to last\" claim is closer to true on the higher-spec models and closer to ordinary on the entry-tier Bravos / Maxima / Centennial. Our techs see Maytag laundry every week, the Commercial-Technology MVWP washers do hold up notably better than average through year 12-15 with normal maintenance."
  },
  {
    q: "Why does my Maytag washer keep stopping mid-cycle?",
    a: "Three common causes, in diagnostic order. (1) Lid lock fault on Bravos top-load or door lock fault on Maxima front-load, washer believes lid/door has opened and stops the cycle for safety. F26 error code if displayed; sometimes silent. About 50% of mid-cycle stoppage. (2) Drain pump issue, washer can't drain fully and stalls before spin. F02 error code typically shown. About 30% of cases. (3) Unbalanced load detection, washer enters extended re-balance attempts and times out. About 15% of cases. Diagnostic order: visual lid/door inspection, drain pump filter clean (10-minute, no-parts fix on ~40% of these calls), redistribute load. About 30% resolve at the homeowner-troubleshooting layer at no parts cost."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does Maytag washer repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when work is approved. Maytag pricing matches Whirlpool because of the shared platform: lid switch / lid lock (Bravos top-load) $145-$215; drain pump $245-$385; water inlet valve $185-$285; drive belt + shift actuator (Bravos) $185-$345; suspension rod kit (Bravos year 9+) $245-$385; door boot (Maxima front-load) $285-$425; bearing + drum seal (Maxima year 8-12) $585-$880; control panel / keypad assembly $285-$445; main control board (CCU) $345-$525; F11 CCU+MCU diagnostic and replacement $345-$680. Commercial-Technology MVWP premium uplift: 10-15% above standard band because of heavier-duty components."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Maytag washers in Sherman Oaks, Irvine, the Inland Empire, and other parts of SoCal?",
    a: "Yes, Maytag washers have solid distribution across our 5-county service area, with concentrations in production-builder homes throughout the Inland Empire (Rancho Cucamonga, Fontana, Ontario), Sherman Oaks and the broader San Fernando Valley single-family market, plus the older Westside neighborhoods (Westwood, parts of Brentwood) where Maytag's reliability reputation has driven buying decisions. Pasadena and Glendale see strong Maxima front-load installations in renovation kitchens. Orange County (Newport Beach, Irvine, Costa Mesa, Tustin) tracks similar mixed patterns. The 8-branch dispatch grid in the hero CTA shows the closest dispatch territory for any address, same parts on truck as Whirlpool, same diagnostic procedures."
  }
];

