<!-- 06 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">06, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Maytag washer jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Two representative service calls, model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Maytag washer service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Maytag MVWB835DW Bravos top-load, Sherman Oaks</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Washer fills and agitates normally but stalls before spin cycle. F26 error code displayed at end of cycle.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Lid lock / lid switch assembly failure, most common Bravos service call (year 4-6 typical, mirrors Whirlpool Cabrio pattern). Switch ohms-out reading inconsistent on bench test, contact intermittent. Drive system tested fine; drain pump tested fine.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Lid lock / lid switch assembly replacement with OEM Whirlpool-platform part (in stock on the truck, same part fits Maytag and Whirlpool Cabrio). Verified normal lid-lock engagement and full cycle progression. F26 cleared.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $185 total. Same-day, 50 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Maytag MHW8630HW Maxima front-load, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Grinding sound during spin cycles, getting louder over the past 4 months. Cycle complete normally; just the noise was the complaint.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Drum bearing wear, typical year 8-10 service item on Maxima (mirrors Whirlpool Duet bearing pattern). Manual drum rotation reproduced grinding; outer tub teardown confirmed worn front bearing and degraded drum seal.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Front bearing + drum seal replacement as a paired set with OEM Whirlpool-platform parts. Always replace both, replacing only the bearing without the seal fails again within months. Verified silent operation on full spin cycle test.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $720 total (parts + labor for tub teardown and rebuild). Same-day, 3.5 hours on-site.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

